# Bucket
countries_bucket = storage.Bucket("countries_info")
# Csv's
general_info_csv = countries_bucket.object("country_general_info.csv")
happiness_info_2015_csv = countries_bucket.object("hapiness_by_year/2015.csv")
happiness_info_2016_csv = countries_bucket.object("hapiness_by_year/2016.csv")
happiness_info_2017_csv = countries_bucket.object("hapiness_by_year/2017.csv")
happiness_info_2018_csv = countries_bucket.object("hapiness_by_year/2018.csv")
happiness_info_2019_csv = countries_bucket.object("hapiness_by_year/2019.csv")

# Dataframes
general = pd.read_csv(io.BytesIO(general_info_csv.read_stream()), delimiter=",", decimal=",")
h_15 = pd.read_csv(io.BytesIO(happiness_info_2015_csv.read_stream()), delimiter=",")

dfs = [general, h_15, h_16, h_17, h_18, h_19]

Znaczenie niektrych kolumn

Arable - % powierzchni kraju mowily do uprawy roli
Crops - % ju wykorzystywany
Agriculture, Industry, Service - udzia % danego sektora w ekonomii
Deathrate - zgony na 1000 osb
Birthrate - urodzenia na 1000 osb
Infant Mortality - zgody na 1000 narodzin
Net migration - imigrants - emigrants / mid year population

Climate meaning

  1. Dry tropical or tundra and ice, classification B and E.
  2. Wet tropical, classification A.
  3. Temperate humid subtropical and temperate continental, classification Cfa, Cwa, and D.
  4. Dry hot summers and wet winters
  5. 1,5 i 2,5 to klimaty porednie midzy 1 i 2 oraz 2 i 3

Interpretacja Heatmap'y

Najwaniejsza dla tego projektu jest ostatni wiersz pokazujcy korelacje Happiness Score / x
Wysokie dodatnie wartoci przy GDP, Literacy i Phones oznaczaj "jedna ronie gdy ronie druga" tzn. Im wysze GDP kraju tym szczliwsi mieszkacy
Analogicznie wysokie ujemne wartoi przy Infant Mortality, Deathrate i Agriculture pokazuj "im wicej ludzi umiera i im wicej rolnikw tym ludzie mniej szczliwi

bucket_name = Context.default().project_id + '-countries-info-exploration-clean'
bucket_path = 'gs://' + bucket_name
bucket_object_15 = bucket_path + '/data_2015.csv'
bucket_object_16 = bucket_path + '/data_2016.csv'
bucket_object_17 = bucket_path + '/data_2017.csv'
bucket_object_18 = bucket_path + '/data_2018.csv'
bucket_object_19 = bucket_path + '/data_2019.csv'

bigquery_dataset_name = 'country_info'
bigquery_table_name_15 = 'data_2015'
bigquery_table_name_16 = 'data_2016'
bigquery_table_name_17 = 'data_2017'
bigquery_table_name_18 = 'data_2018'
bigquery_table_name_19 = 'data_2019'


# Define storage bucket
bucket = storage.Bucket(bucket_name)

# Create storage bucket if it does not exist
if not bucket.exists():
    bucket.create()

# Define BigQuery dataset and table
dataset = bq.Dataset(bigquery_dataset_name)
table_15 = bq.Table(bigquery_dataset_name + '.' + bigquery_table_name_15)
table_16 = bq.Table(bigquery_dataset_name + '.' + bigquery_table_name_16)
table_17 = bq.Table(bigquery_dataset_name + '.' + bigquery_table_name_17)
table_18 = bq.Table(bigquery_dataset_name + '.' + bigquery_table_name_18)
table_19 = bq.Table(bigquery_dataset_name + '.' + bigquery_table_name_19)


# Create BigQuery dataset
if not dataset.exists():
    dataset.create()

# Create or overwrite the existing table if it exists
table_schema_15 = bq.Schema.from_data(mh_15)
table_schema_16 = bq.Schema.from_data(mh_16)
table_schema_17 = bq.Schema.from_data(mh_17)
table_schema_18 = bq.Schema.from_data(mh_18)
table_schema_19 = bq.Schema.from_data(mh_19)

table_15.create(schema = table_schema_15, overwrite = True)
table_16.create(schema = table_schema_16, overwrite = True)
table_17.create(schema = table_schema_17, overwrite = True)
table_18.create(schema = table_schema_18, overwrite = True)
table_19.create(schema = table_schema_19, overwrite = True)


# Write the DataFrame to GCS (Google Cloud Storage)
%storage write --variable mh_15 --object $bucket_object_15 --content_type text/csv
%storage write --variable mh_16 --object $bucket_object_16 --content_type text/csv
